---
/**
 * Gameplay Guide Page - How to Play Bloom
 * SEO-focused page targeting "how to play bloom", "bloom gameplay guide", "extraction fps guide"
 */
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import factionsData from '@/data/factions.json';

// Get Truce Wardens for beginner recommendation
const wardensFaction = factionsData.factions.find((f) => f.id === 'FCT_CWD');
---

<!-- Canon: Gameplay overview. Keep in sync with BLOOM_GAME_BIBLE.md for tone (grounded salvage, IEZ/Dead Sky) and ROADMAP.md for EA scope. -->
<BaseLayout
  title="How to Play Bloom - Gameplay Guide & Tutorial | Bloom Extraction FPS"
  description="Master the extraction shooter gameplay of Bloom. Learn core mechanics, match flow, faction abilities, and beginner tips for this grounded post-apocalyptic salvage FPS set in the Inner Exclusion Zone."
  type="article"
>
  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container">
      <h1 class="hero-title">How to Play Bloom</h1>
      <p class="hero-tagline">
        Master the extraction shooter that turns desperate salvage runs into survival stories
      </p>
      <p class="hero-description">
        Bloom is a grounded extraction FPS about hauling warped tech out of a collapsing Earth. This
        guide walks you through raid flow, faction roles, and squad habits that keep your convoy
        alive long enough to see the next deployment.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What is an Extraction FPS -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="section-title">What is an Extraction FPS?</h2>
      <div class="content-block">
        <p class="lead">
          Bloom is an <strong>extraction shooter</strong> set around the Inner Exclusion Zone - a high-stakes
          PvPvE genre where squads deploy into hostile biomes, compete for salvage, and must extract
          before the Zone or rival crews tear them apart.
        </p>

        <div class="extraction-flow">
          <div class="flow-step">
            <div class="step-number">1</div>
            <h3>Deploy</h3>
            <p>Enter the biome with your squad and gear</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flow-arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</div>
          <div class="flow-step">
            <div class="step-number">2</div>
            <h3>Loot</h3>
            <p>Gather resources and complete objectives</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flow-arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</div>
          <div class="flow-step">
            <div class="step-number">3</div>
            <h3>Extract or Die</h3>
            <p>Reach extraction or lose everything</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="callout callout-warning">
          <h4>Risk vs Reward</h4>
          <p>
            The longer you stay in a raid, the more resources you can gather - but the greater the
            risk of encountering rival players, hostile enemies, and running out of time. <strong
              >Every decision matters</strong
            > because death means losing your equipped gear (similar to Escape from Tarkov).
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="comparison-box">
          <h4>Compared to Other Extraction Games</h4>
          <ul>
            <li>
              <strong>Like Escape from Tarkov</strong>: Full-loot death penalty, hardcore survival
              mechanics
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Like Hunt: Showdown</strong>: Objective-based gameplay with extraction tension
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Unique to Bloom</strong>: A 10-faction system built around roles and trust,
              plus a shared salvage economy where every raid feeds back into your convoy, alliances,
              and long-term survival.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Inner Exclusion Zone (IEZ) 101 -->
  <section class="section section-dark">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="section-title">Inner Exclusion Zone (IEZ) 101</h2>
      <div class="content-block">
        <p class="lead">
          The Inner Exclusion Zone – the Dead Sky – is a roughly 200km radius of collapsed
          infrastructure, Harvester wreckage, and phase anomalies. It is where every raid in Bloom
          takes place.
        </p>

        <div class="iez-grid">
          <div class="iez-card">
            <h3>Hardness Rings (H1–H5)</h3>
            <p>
              The IEZ is divided into hardness rings. H1 and H2 are “training grounds” on the
              fringe, while H3–H5 push into increasingly lethal territory closer to the Monolith
              scars.
            </p>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>H1–H2:</strong> Safer routes, beginner-friendly raids.</li>
              <li><strong>H3–H4:</strong> High-value salvage, heavy threats.</li>
              <li><strong>H5:</strong> “If you go here, you’re either ready or dead.”</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="iez-card">
            <h3>Factions & Convoys</h3>
            <p>
              Factions carve out lanes into the IEZ, running convoys between Gates, depots, and
              field positions. No one group controls everything – food, routes, medicine, and intel
              are split across crews.
            </p>
            <ul>
              <li>Directorate holds artillery and heavy infrastructure.</li>
              <li>Vultures live off wrecks, dead convoys, and forgotten caches.</li>
              <li>Wardens stabilize protection zones around Gates and metros.</li>
              <li>The Seventy-Seven trade contracts, favors, and firepower.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="iez-card">
            <h3>Harvester Pressure</h3>
            <p>
              Harvester systems are not villains with faces – they are automated defenses and failed
              machines. Their drones, Monolith echoes, and phase pockets shape every raid without
              turning the world into pure fantasy.
            </p>
            <ul>
              <li>Phase anomalies that bend time and space in small areas.</li>
              <li>Quietus marks that punish repeated failure in the same place.</li>
              <li>Wreck sites that offer huge payoff at huge risk.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Match Flow -->
  <section class="section section-dark">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="section-title">Match Flow: Every Raid Follows These Steps</h2>

      <div class="match-flow">
        <div class="match-step">
          <div class="step-icon">
            <svg
              xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
              fill="none"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              stroke="currentColor"
            >
              <path
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                stroke-width="2"
                d="M16 7a4 4 0 11-8 0 4 4 0 018 0zM12 14a7 7 0 00-7 7h14a7 7 0 00-7-7z"></path>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <div class="step-content">
            <h3><span class="step-label">Phase 1:</span> Loadout</h3>
            <p>
              Choose your faction, select weapons and gear, form your squad (1-4 players), and
              prepare for deployment.
            </p>
            <ul>
              <li>Pick faction based on your playstyle (tank, medic, scout, etc.)</li>
              <li>Equip weapons, armor, medical supplies, and ammo</li>
              <li>Risk more valuable gear for better performance</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="match-step">
          <div class="step-icon">
            <svg
              xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
              fill="none"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              stroke="currentColor"
            >
              <path
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                stroke-width="2"
                d="M17.657 16.657L13.414 20.9a1.998 1.998 0 01-2.827 0l-4.244-4.243a8 8 0 1111.314 0z"
              ></path>
              <path
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                stroke-width="2"
                d="M15 11a3 3 0 11-6 0 3 3 0 016 0z"></path>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <div class="step-content">
            <h3><span class="step-label">Phase 2:</span> Deployment</h3>
            <p>Drop into the biome with your squad at a chosen spawn location.</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Select spawn point strategically (near loot vs. safer locations)</li>
              <li>Coordinate with squad on initial objectives</li>
              <li>Match timer begins (typically 25-40 minutes)</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="match-step">
          <div class="step-icon">
            <svg
              xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
              fill="none"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              stroke="currentColor"
            >
              <path
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                stroke-width="2"
                d="M21 21l-6-6m2-5a7 7 0 11-14 0 7 7 0 0114 0z"></path>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <div class="step-content">
            <h3><span class="step-label">Phase 3:</span> Exploration</h3>
            <p>
              Loot containers, gather resources, complete objectives, and navigate biome hazards.
            </p>
            <ul>
              <li>Search buildings, caches, and hidden stashes</li>
              <li>Complete faction-specific objectives for bonus rewards</li>
              <li>Manage inventory weight and ammunition</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="match-step">
          <div class="step-icon">
            <svg
              xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
              fill="none"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              stroke="currentColor"
            >
              <path
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                stroke-width="2"
                d="M12 9v2m0 4h.01m-6.938 4h13.856c1.54 0 2.502-1.667 1.732-3L13.732 4c-.77-1.333-2.694-1.333-3.464 0L3.34 16c-.77 1.333.192 3 1.732 3z"
              ></path>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <div class="step-content">
            <h3><span class="step-label">Phase 4:</span> Combat</h3>
            <p>Engage rival players, AI enemies, and hostile factions in tactical firefights.</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Fight other player squads for resources and territory</li>
              <li>Defend against PvE threats (Forged, mutants, wildlife)</li>
              <li>Use faction abilities to gain combat advantages</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="match-step">
          <div class="step-icon">
            <svg
              xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
              fill="none"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              stroke="currentColor"
            >
              <path
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                stroke-width="2"
                d="M13 7h8m0 0v8m0-8l-8 8-4-4-6 6"></path>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <div class="step-content">
            <h3><span class="step-label">Phase 5:</span> Extraction</h3>
            <p>Reach an extraction point before the timer expires to keep your loot.</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Navigate to available extraction points (marked on map)</li>
              <li>Defend extraction zone during countdown (15-30 seconds)</li>
              <li>Extract before match timer runs out</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="match-step">
          <div class="step-icon">
            <svg
              xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
              fill="none"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              stroke="currentColor"
            >
              <path
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                stroke-width="2"
                d="M9 12l2 2 4-4M7.835 4.697a3.42 3.42 0 001.946-.806 3.42 3.42 0 014.438 0 3.42 3.42 0 001.946.806 3.42 3.42 0 013.138 3.138 3.42 3.42 0 00.806 1.946 3.42 3.42 0 010 4.438 3.42 3.42 0 00-.806 1.946 3.42 3.42 0 01-3.138 3.138 3.42 3.42 0 00-1.946.806 3.42 3.42 0 01-4.438 0 3.42 3.42 0 00-1.946-.806 3.42 3.42 0 01-3.138-3.138 3.42 3.42 0 00-.806-1.946 3.42 3.42 0 010-4.438 3.42 3.42 0 00.806-1.946 3.42 3.42 0 013.138-3.138z"
              ></path>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <div class="step-content">
            <h3><span class="step-label">Phase 6:</span> Results</h3>
            <p>Review your haul and experience gains - or mourn your losses.</p>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Successful extraction:</strong> Keep all looted items and gain XP</li>
              <li><strong>Death:</strong> Lose equipped gear (weapons, armor, items)</li>
              <li>
                <strong>Timeout:</strong> Lose everything if you don't extract before time expires
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Core Mechanics -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="section-title">Core Mechanics</h2>

      <div class="mechanics-grid">
        <div class="mechanic-card">
          <h3>
            <svg
              xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
              fill="none"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              stroke="currentColor"
            >
              <path
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                stroke-width="2"
                d="M17 20h5v-2a3 3 0 00-5.356-1.857M17 20H7m10 0v-2c0-.656-.126-1.283-.356-1.857M7 20H2v-2a3 3 0 015.356-1.857M7 20v-2c0-.656.126-1.283.356-1.857m0 0a5.002 5.002 0 019.288 0M15 7a3 3 0 11-6 0 3 3 0 016 0zm6 3a2 2 0 11-4 0 2 2 0 014 0zM7 10a2 2 0 11-4 0 2 2 0 014 0z"
              ></path>
            </svg>
            Faction System
          </h3>
          <p>
            Across Early Access and 1.0, Bloom builds toward <strong
              >10 interconnected factions</strong
            >, each with distinct abilities, playstyles, and roles in the Dead Sky. At EA you start
            with four core factions, then expand into more specialized crews as the roster grows.
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Each faction has 3 unique abilities (1 passive, 2 active)</li>
            <li>Squad bonuses activate when playing with teammates</li>
            <li>Faction progression unlocks better gear and abilities</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="mechanic-card">
          <h3>
            <svg
              xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
              fill="none"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              stroke="currentColor"
            >
              <path
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                stroke-width="2"
                d="M12 4.354a4 4 0 110 5.292M15 21H3v-1a6 6 0 0112 0v1zm0 0h6v-1a6 6 0 00-9-5.197M13 7a4 4 0 11-8 0 4 4 0 018 0z"
              ></path>
            </svg>
            Squad Play
          </h3>
          <p>
            Team up with <strong>1-4 players</strong> to leverage faction synergies and squad abilities.
            Coordinated teams have massive advantages over solo players.
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Mix factions for balanced team composition (tank + medic + scout + DPS)</li>
            <li>Share resources and revive downed teammates</li>
            <li>Squad-wide buffs from faction abilities</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="mechanic-card">
          <h3>
            <svg
              xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
              fill="none"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              stroke="currentColor"
            >
              <path
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                stroke-width="2"
                d="M3.055 11H5a2 2 0 012 2v1a2 2 0 002 2 2 2 0 012 2v2.945M8 3.935V5.5A2.5 2.5 0 0010.5 8h.5a2 2 0 012 2 2 2 0 104 0 2 2 0 012-2h1.064M15 20.488V18a2 2 0 012-2h3.064M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"
              ></path>
            </svg>
            Biome Hazards
          </h3>
          <p>
            Each biome inside the Inner Exclusion Zone layers <strong
              >environmental challenges</strong
            > on top of enemy threats: extreme cold, toxic clouds, radiation zones, and hostile weather
            that can wipe a convoy faster than a gunfight.
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Threat levels range from H1 (safe) to H5 (deadly)</li>
            <li>Certain factions perform better in their home biomes</li>
            <li>Environmental gear provides protection from hazards</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="mechanic-card">
          <h3>
            <svg
              xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
              fill="none"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              stroke="currentColor"
            >
              <path
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                stroke-width="2"
                d="M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12"></path>
            </svg>
            Death Penalty
          </h3>
          <p>
            <strong>Full-loot death system</strong> similar to Escape from Tarkov. If you die, you lose
            all equipped gear - but items in your secure container are safe.
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Lose weapons, armor, medical supplies, and inventory items</li>
            <li>Secure container (limited slots) protects valuable items</li>
            <li>Insurance can recover gear if not looted by enemies</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="mechanic-card">
          <h3>
            <svg
              xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
              fill="none"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              stroke="currentColor"
            >
              <path
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                stroke-width="2"
                d="M20 7l-8-4-8 4m16 0l-8 4m8-4v10l-8 4m0-10L4 7m8 4v10M4 7v10l8 4"></path>
            </svg>
            Resource Management
          </h3>
          <p>
            Manage limited <strong>inventory space, ammunition, health, and stamina</strong>. Every
            decision about what to carry affects your survival chances.
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Weight affects movement speed and stamina drain</li>
            <li>Medical supplies are limited - heal strategically</li>
            <li>Ammo management critical in extended firefights</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="mechanic-card">
          <h3>
            <svg
              xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
              fill="none"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              stroke="currentColor"
            >
              <path
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                stroke-width="2"
                d="M13 10V3L4 14h7v7l9-11h-7z"></path>
            </svg>
            PvPvE Combat
          </h3>
          <p>
            Face threats from <strong>both players and AI enemies</strong>. Rival squads hunt for
            loot while hostile Forged, mutants, and wildlife roam the wasteland.
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Tactical gunplay with realistic ballistics</li>
            <li>AI enemies guard high-value loot locations</li>
            <li>Dynamic encounters - every raid is different</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- First 10 Minutes Tutorial -->
  <section class="section section-dark">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="section-title">Your First 10 Minutes: Beginner Tutorial</h2>

      <div class="tutorial-intro">
        <p class="lead">
          New to extraction shooters or Bloom? This step-by-step guide will walk you through your
          first successful raid. Follow these steps to learn the basics and extract with loot.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="tutorial-steps">
        <div class="tutorial-step">
          <div class="tutorial-number">Step 1</div>
          <div class="tutorial-content">
            <h3>Choose Truce Wardens (Defender)</h3>
            <p>
              For your first raid, pick <strong>{wardensFaction?.shortName}</strong> - the beginner-friendly
              defender faction. Their defensive bonuses and protection zones make them forgiving for
              new players.
            </p>
            <div class="faction-highlight">
              <strong>Why Wardens?</strong>
              <ul>
                <li>Protection Zone bonuses near Gates and Metro nodes (survive longer)</li>
                <li>Defensive fortifications for cover</li>
                <li>Team support role - valuable in any squad</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="tutorial-step">
          <div class="tutorial-number">Step 2</div>
          <div class="tutorial-content">
            <h3>Equip Basic Loadout</h3>
            <p>
              Start with <strong>starter gear</strong> - you'll get this for free, so there's no risk.
              Don't bring expensive gear until you've learned the basics.
            </p>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Weapon:</strong> Basic assault rifle (balanced, easy to control)</li>
              <li><strong>Armor:</strong> Level 1 vest (some protection, light weight)</li>
              <li><strong>Medical:</strong> 2x bandages, 1x medkit</li>
              <li><strong>Ammo:</strong> 3-4 magazines (120-160 rounds)</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="tutorial-step">
          <div class="tutorial-number">Step 3</div>
          <div class="tutorial-content">
            <h3>Deploy to Forest Hills (Safe Biome)</h3>
            <p>
              Choose <strong>Forest Hills</strong> - a H1 (low threat) biome perfect for learning. Spawn
              at the southern edge for a safe starting position.
            </p>
            <div class="callout callout-tip">
              <strong>Pro Tip:</strong> Play solo for your first raid to learn at your own pace. You
              can join squads once you understand the basics.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="tutorial-step">
          <div class="tutorial-number">Step 4</div>
          <div class="tutorial-content">
            <h3>Follow Basic Loot Route</h3>
            <p>
              Stick to this <strong>beginner-friendly route</strong> that avoids high-traffic areas:
            </p>
            <ol>
              <li>Spawn → Move to nearest small building cluster</li>
              <li>Loot 2-3 buildings (avoid large compounds - they attract players)</li>
              <li>Grab medical supplies, ammo, and basic resources</li>
              <li>Don't be greedy - aim for 50% inventory full</li>
            </ol>
            <div class="callout callout-warning">
              <strong>Avoid:</strong> Military bases, major landmarks, and supply drops in your first
              raid. These attract experienced players.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="tutorial-step">
          <div class="tutorial-number">Step 5</div>
          <div class="tutorial-content">
            <h3>Find Extraction Point</h3>
            <p>
              After 10-15 minutes of looting, head to an <strong>extraction point</strong>:
            </p>
            <ul>
              <li>Press M to open map and locate extraction markers (green helicopter icons)</li>
              <li>Choose the closest extraction to minimize travel time</li>
              <li>Approach cautiously - other players may be camping extractions</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="tutorial-step">
          <div class="tutorial-number">Step 6</div>
          <div class="tutorial-content">
            <h3>Secure Extraction</h3>
            <p>
              Enter the extraction zone and <strong>wait for the countdown</strong> (20 seconds):
            </p>
            <ul>
              <li>Stay in the marked area (yellow circle)</li>
              <li>Watch for enemy players approaching</li>
              <li>Once timer completes, you're out - loot secured!</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="success-box">
              <strong>Congratulations!</strong> You've completed your first extraction. Review your loot,
              sell unwanted items, and prepare for your next raid.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Tips for New Players -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="section-title">Essential Tips for New Players</h2>

      <div class="tips-grid">
        <div class="tip-card">
          <div class="tip-icon">1</div>
          <h3>Start with Safe Biomes</h3>
          <p>
            Focus on <strong>H1 and H2 threat level biomes</strong> (Forest Hills, Central Grasslands)
            until you're comfortable with combat and navigation. Higher threat biomes have better loot
            but far more danger.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="tip-card">
          <div class="tip-icon">2</div>
          <h3>Play Support Roles First</h3>
          <p>
            Begin with <strong>defender or tank factions</strong> (Wardens, Directorate). These roles
            are valuable to any squad and more forgiving than aggressive DPS or stealth factions.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="tip-card">
          <div class="tip-icon">3</div>
          <h3>Don't Be Greedy</h3>
          <p>
            <strong>Extract early</strong> when you have moderate loot. Many new players die trying to
            fill their inventory completely. A successful extraction with half-full bags is better than
            dying with a full inventory.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="tip-card">
          <div class="tip-icon">4</div>
